I moved to Burbank from the east coast and stopped by City Salon Spa. I met Joanna and she is very sweet and kind. I don’t trust just anyone with my eyebrows anymore as I’ve had some terrible experiences. But she showed me her work and I believed she would do a good job.

Joanna is the best! Go see her!<//text>

<Text>BEST DEEP CLEANING FACIAL AND MICRO-NEEDLING IN ALL OF CALIFORNIA!!! (Not just a cheap facial massage—but an actual cleaning)

After having lunch with a friend Downtown Burbank, I came across City Salon Spa, I was visiting in town and my eyebrows were overdue for a wax, so I decided to walk-in. I was pleasantly greeted by Joanna, she was very welcoming and I was blown away a such a good price I decided to let her do my brows. Joanna was very kind and knowledgeable about brows and shaping them to my face, she also took her time and exceeded my expectations so much that my friend ended up getting her brows done as well! While my friend was getting her brows done, I noticed Joanna was also a facial specialist and I had been looking for someone who specialized in pigmented skin. Joanna took the time to explain how deep cleaning facial and microdermabrasion lightens scars and dark pigmentation, so I decided to get both the deep cleaning facial and microdermabrasion. The prices are the best I’ve found in all of California and her services exceeded my expectations once again. She’s very gentle, I have very sensitive skin but there was no irritation after my services. After receiving only one treatment most of my acne scars were gone, the dark pigmentation has visibly lightened and my skin is glowing!!! I will be returning and so will my friend.< /Text>< pics>

Brakes front and rear, inner/outer tie rods, upper/lower ball joints, wheel bearings, full brake flush, oil change and alignment.

I had a couple questions with the service and without hesitation they took care of it to accommodate me- no argument just a care for 110% customer satisfaction.

Great group of service Tech's, energy and environment.

*if you have a concern respectfully ask - no one shop is perfect

< text>
It good for what it is. Definitely catering to a certain aspects of the tourist crowd as far as spice level. The flavor is good but I wouldn't mind a little more heat. I liked the burritos we ordered for take out tonight. They were stuffed with chicken and not just loaded with beans and rice like some places do to cut costs. I'd definitely order again and I'd like to try some other menu items. Tonight we played it safe with burritos because that's my go to order at a new Mexican place. Also I could (should?) only eat half so I've got some lunch tomorrow. Thanks for a filling meal at a good price.</text>

<text>We arrived about 4:30. There were four of us. my elderly in-laws, my husband, and myself. Parking can be very tricky. There's no parking lot or structure. Luckily we found a spot right up front.

Very cute  decor inside. Bright and festive. There's a bar just in the center as you walk in, and tables all around. It was EXTREMELY loud inside. The entire time, we had to tell, to converse.

Our server was nice, but distracted. We had to ask for many things, multiple time, because she would forget. Little things like my sour cream, my father in laws guacamole. Our to go box.

They were out of tamales. Out of root beer. I know, these things happen. Just a slight annoyance. The ambiance was just off. The chairs are SUPER comfy thought. Bathroom was clean.

I got the taco and sopas plate. Came with beans and rice. Beans and rice were ok. Kinda bland. Nothing special. The taco was 2 bites. Super tiny. A bit dry, but good. I never had a sopas, and it was weird. Whatever the little round thing at the bottom was, was rubbery and hard to cut. Everything was drowning in lettuce. Although, the salad dressing was delicious!

Hubby got 2 soft tacos and an enchiladas plate. He didn't care for the enchilada. The sauce wasn't great. Tacos were basic.

Dad got a pork burrito. He liked it. But he eats anything. Mom got a taco and chile relleno. She liked it, but didn't love it. She didn't say much, but she ate most of it.

Wasn't a terrible place, but given the overall experience, I don't think we will go back.< /text><gmap_id>0x8080354faaaaaaab:0x12fa86bfac99deaf</gmap_id><Date>1539217167392</Date>< pictures>

< user_name>
Casey Russell<//user_name>
< time>
1544885977191<//time>
< Rate>
2< /Rate>
< text>
I was a faithful customer of Los Gallitos for over a decade at their old location next to Lucy's laundromat. I was going to try their new spot a few months back, but when I opened the door I was hit by a wall of noise, and opted for takeout.
Tonight I figured would be a good time to try being that it's not tourist season and they weren't busy. We walked in and it was loud, but what I noticed most was the overpowering smell of leather. They have really cool handmade chairs bound in leather that are very comfortable, but for me, detract from the olfactory experience.
Our service wasn't as good as before, and the order was slightly off. The menu hasn't changed, and the food is still good basic Mexican fare. My burrito was slightly cold and came on a plastic plate. My better half had a real plate and her food was plenty hot. Strange.
She got change at their cash register for a $20 bill in order to leave a decent tip, returned to our table only to find it was change for a ten. She told the waitress, who with sneer said, no it was a ten. They went back and forth a bit, and when the cash drawer was finally opened there was a $20 bill in the ten slot. Embarrassing.
This just isn't the same restaurant I loved. There's not the hole-in-the-wall, quaint experience that kept me coming back for so many years. You used to walk in and they would say, 'sit anywhere.' Now you wait to be seated next to the constant noise of a margarita blender. Change is like that, and I know a restaurant's success can be off-putting to regulars. I hope that they're still ironing out the kinks. The owners and staff are some of the kindest folks around and I wish them the best, but from now on I will be getting my order to go.</text>

<Review>Being a landscaping novice who only needs to service one single family home, I realize I'm not the "ideal" customer for places like Bonnett who cater to contractors and professionals.  I've been to a couple other irrigation places in the area and never got the information needed to make sure I was getting the correct parts in the sizes I needed to effectively water my yard while conserving as much water as possible. I was a bit apprehensive when I pulled into Bonnett because it looked like the other contractor-centered irrigation places I'd been to. The staff here was EXTREMELY HELPFUL though! After visiting Bonnett I feel like I'll have the right parts even if I don't have a clue what I'm doing. Unlike other places the staff made suggestions and offered options rather than just selling me whatever I thought I needed. Bonnett is my new go-to for my landscaping needs, whatever those may be.</Review><Name>Jenny Frank</Name><response>None</response>< user_id>

Place is amazing, really loved the food. I got the number 8 which has pretty much everything you really need in my opinion, but my brother got the falafel which according to him were pretty delicious especially with hummus that comes with it and the best part is that it is very affordable.

< Text>
Came here for the first time today. I was very impressed with the quality of meat they have. Meat was very tender and flavorful. Delicious. It was served with my choice of rice, hummus and salad and a delicious side of a grilled tomato. They have very friendly staff. Very cute restaurant. Trendy. TV's on the wall and communal tables. Only thing I would improve is to have a jug of water for customers so we dont have to keep on asking for cups of water everytime we run out especially if the restaurant gets busy. It becomes very annoying to the worker and ourselves to keep asking for a cup of water. Or just make the cups slightly bigger. Besides this I love this restaurant. Definitely will return.<//Text>

<user_name>Kay< /user_name>< review>
Maurice runs a tight ship with some of the best Lebanese food in town. The location is new, clean and maintained well but you come here for the food. Juicy, moist and perfectly flavored shawarma, succulent beef kabob, crispy fries, fresh salad, perfect tabouleh, flavorful hummus and toum. No matter what you’re in the mood for - even the wings - Al Basch delivers and delivers with consistency. Jose who manages the day to day is also a very hard worker who cares about every customer, so nothing but excellence from Al Basch day in and day out. You’ll never leave disappointed when you visit Al Basch - the best of the best.< /review>

< username>
Brendan Farrell<//username>
< Date>
1513321190972<//Date>
< Rate>
4< /Rate>
< text>
After walking in and placing our order, we realized they were closing in 5 minutes! The staff were very friendly despite us ordering so late. We realized our mistake and changed our order to take out (so that we didn't keep them there after closing) but they were very polite and offered us to stay.

We ordered two chicken shawarma plates, swapping the salad for fries on one order. The chicken was ok, a bit dry and underseasoned, though we did order just before closing time. The garlic sauce was delicious and helped improve the chicken. There was a large amount of rice under the top layer of chicken, which was a little disappointing. The plates came with a good amount of salad (or fries!) and hummus, though the hummus was a little bland. They also included a bag of pita bread with our order - not sure if they always do this, or if they were giving it away at the end of the day. Either way, it was a nice bonus!

The drink selection was good, with lots of options in the cooler. The interior was new and clean, with fun Christmas and Hannukuh decorations placed around.

Overall, this new spot has great service, but the food was a little more bland than other Mediterranean places I've tried. Looking forward to coming back (closer to normal dinner time) and trying more of their menu!< /text>

< review>
Okay I'm going to try to make a long story short I have been having back problems since I was 14 and was told by a doctor from Kaiser at the time that I would have problems walking when I was in my mid-30s. I am now 33 and my situation has gone worse, to the point that my back would spasm, arms would go numb and hip would go out. Was in pain every single day and could barely sleep at night, I start to see another doctor again to see what we can do. After multiple MRIS and CAT scans I was told that I have bulging disc in my neck and lower back and there's something wrong with my hip but that because of my age this was normal and there was nothing they can do about it. The only thing that my doctor suggested was to go see a pain management specialist. After letting the pain management specialist know that I did not want narcotics to mask the pain because I do not like taking pills I was told that I was "medication ignorant" and I should probably go see a physical therapist. Mind you this is with her not even looking at my chart. I went to see a physical therapist and was told the best thing for me to do was just to start working out. With really no other options I decide to go see a chiropractor and that's when I met Dylan Casteel. The first thing I can say is he was the first person to actually listen to what problems I was having and gave me realistic options to help fix it. He never once talk bad about the doctors that had see me prior to him, he just let me know that they weren't give me all my options. I have seen him once every two weeks for the last 4 months and can honestly say without a shadow of a doubt that I feel 100% better. I know some people may find it hard to believe because of the stigma with chiropractors but I am just giving you my honest opinion Dr. Casteel has helped me more than all the other professionals I have met. I even referred my mother to him who's doctors are giving her the only option to fuse her lower spine. After one visit with Dr. Casteel she couldn't stop singing his praises by the way that he listened to her and helped her. Also my mother has worked in the medical field for over 20 years. I know this was a long review just wanted to put it out there because it really has changed my life and I hope that anybody who is having these type of problems takes the time to go see him to help take care of your situations. All you have to do is call Monique at the front office to set up an appointment she's an amazing person and makes sure that she contacts you the day before your appointment every time to remind you. Big thank you again to Valley Health Team.</review>

<UserId.>115466732823955581539<//UserId.><Name>Kristy O<//Name>< Date>
1620583310454<//Date>
<Rating>1</Rating>< text>
⚠️ CAUTION⚠️
Don't bother coming here or bringing your loved ones here to get yours or their nails done. As a mother to be, I brought my mom, mom in law, and sisters to this place for an early Mother's day gift. Like the other reviews state, they have poor customer service (read until the end), they hike up their prices when they feel like it, and don't honor appointment times especially for groups.

Have an appointment time?
They make you wait for their services while they prioritize walk-ins.

Adding a person to your party?
Don't bother. Especially if you're the party host who is paying the bill and looking to add yourself for a quick manicure, they will make you wait while they take care of other people that walked in after you without an appointment time (just to make more money).

How much do they actually charge?
They don't have set prices and charge you more for their rude and unprofessional service. Even if you asked what service you would like and given a price chart, they still charge you extra and hide the price chart they originally showed you. At the register they won't even give you a bill showing the total cost break down. My party was only supposed to pay $120 according to their price chart they showed us plus we should have been discounted for the mistreatment, long wait time to be worked on, and terrible service. Instead they charged $150.

Special offers/discounts?
Not this place. They will charge you more for it just being the day before a holiday. They will even claim the higher price is because you came on a holiday. Most nail salons I and my family have been to offer group discounts, holiday specials, and great customer service to keep their customers coming and leaving happy.

Customer service?
If you're not happy with their services, they will argue with you to pay full price plus extra. They will literally hold you hostage until you pay their price for services you and your party were 100% unsatisfied with. They will even call the cops only for the cops to tell the owner/manager they are wrong for mistreating the paying customers.

Getting a manicure?
Don't bother. When they know they screwed up on your nails, they will cover their childish paint job with glitter and make it look worst than it already was. They will carelessly wipe your nails when they're still wet with a towel leaving lint on your nails. You will have cracks, smudges, thick uneven nail polish layers, and bumps on your nails. They don't even apply nail polish to the entire nail.

Getting a pedicure?
Don't bother. They will leave you waiting in cold water long enough to get wrinkly feet, while they take care of walk-ins. When they do come back to you they will burn your feet with hot water instead of checking the temperature.

Getting cuticles and dead skin removed?
Don't bother. They will leave you with cuts and tears all over.

Making a group appointment time with your family or friends?
Don't bother. They will only take care of one person from your party at a time while they take care of multiple walk-ins. If you walk back and forth to check on each of your party members, they will rudely stare and complain. Also, if you have a group appointment time, they might take one person in your party early, but the rest of your group will wait until their unprofessional techs feel like offering a seat and working on their nails. And if your group members are seated they will make each of your party members wait to be serviced while they prioritize walk-ins.<//text>

If I could give this place zero stars, I would do so.
Very rude staff, poor quality, and they don’t have fixed prices. They want to charge you as much as they can. My daughter did acrylic nails, and after a week  they start to fall off. After 10 days, all of the nails fell off completely. You can barely see any acrylic used on the nails. When we went back to them, they said that’s because she has short nails so the acrylic nails didn’t stay long time and fell off. That’s the weirdest answer I ever heard. My daughter used to do acrylic nails for 3 years now and they always last at least a month. But the place she used to go ran out of business because of covid.
This place is a waist of time and money. It was our first and last time there. We’ll never go back.</Review>

<Text>This was my first visit to this nail salon for a manicure.  I made an appointment, and service was timely.  My Manicurist was Ki who was so unprofessional there isn't even a word to describe her.  Not only did she fail the first rule of customer service, which is to introduce oneself, she then spent more time looking at her cell phone and reading her messages than looking at my nails while she was working on them.  I seriously thought she was reading directions on how to do a manicure.

Unfortunately, her lack of care and service is what shows in the end.  I had long healthy natural nails going in, and even though I showed her very specifically what length to shorten them to, I left with nothing more than nubs; jagged ones at that!  I also specifically told her I wanted them the same shape; semi-rounded, not square.  Well, I guess she doesn't know the difference.  My jagged nubs are square, which makes sense because she cut and filed them so short, there was nothing left to round.  The so-called massage was a joke, maybe 30 seconds on one hand, and 18 on the other.  Because of this unprofessional, unskilled, careless and rude employee, I would give this business negative stars if it was an option.

I did inform the girl at the front desk who took my money (full price by the way), had her feel the jagged nubs, and look at the length.  She agreed this was poor quality.  She stated she would inform the owner because this is not the quality they want to be portrayed.  No offer to have someone fix it; probably because there is no way to fix it other than time to allow them to grow again.   No offer of a refund or discount, but there was an apology, which I will try and remember as I smooth out the jagged nubs and wait for them to grow out so I can get them back to the length and shape they were before this nightmare.

Overall the salon was clean and tidy, but files were previously used and it is unknown whether required sanitizing is up to code.  I've been to other salons where they actually open a  sealed package of sterilized tools in front of you and they were less money than what I spent at this place.

Obviously, I would never return to this salon, nor would I recommend the place to anyone else.</Text>< user_id>

<date>1622500202279<//date>< Text>
Very clean. They are keeping the social distancing standards and skipping seats. The seats are amazing and confortable. The sound is crisp and the picture is quality. The staff is in a good mood. Very enjoyable experience. It's inside the mall so you can walk around afterwards. Parking is great. You can park extremely close to the entrance of the mall and just walk a little to get to the theater as the theater is inside the mall. There's an alcohol bar inside too- nice little spot for the adults!< /Text>

< text>
It's a nice theater 🎥 😁. If it's just you and your favorite person, then I recommend this location. A Small theater and because of covid the seating are 2 seats apart which is good if you wanna whisper to your partner and talk about the movie. If you plan on watching a movie with more than 2 people then I suggest ordering online so you can choose seats near eachother. Or you can just spread out in the theater room. Harkins and Edward's Cinema would be better for a movie night or day with a group of friends or family. You can do that with this theater as well, but less seats.</text>

<userid>102582790159773457219</userid>< name>
Lorna Mendez< /name>
<time>1562988667431< /time><rating>4< /rating>< text>
The line was huge, should of had more open.  Had to wait 25 minutes to get food, missed a lot if previews.  Had to send in most everyone else while I waited.  I found out it's better to order on the app 1/2 hour ahead of time.  And get the Premiere Stubs Rewards for free upgrades, no $2 fee when reserving seats for the movie.  People were having to sit in the front row for a 9:15 movie.  The chicken fingers were a lot but not crispy, probably because they were trying to do so many and get them out fast.  Popcorn was good, and the nachos (chips and cheese) was 2 big cheese cups and a big box of chips; twice as much as you get from Regal.  All in all we will go back, just order ahead of time.  Oh, and the 4 - 5 employees that I talked to were all nice and trying to do the best they could with so much going on.<//text>

< Text>
My go-to theatre locally.  Actually to be honest, this is the ONLY theatre I go to locally.  There are several theatres closer to me, but the other theatres don't have reclining seats, are not as roomy, nor as comfortable.  I've been spoiled by some of the theatres that I used to go to when I was in the south bay area so now this is the only one I've been to so far that can live up to my expectations.

However, the prices do reflect this.  Other theatres may be slightly cheaper.  This theatre has discounts on Tuesdays though and there are other ways to get that theatre fix here at discounted prices...besides the prices are no more than what I used to pay in south bay.  This theatre is best in the area so far for me.< /Text>

<Text>Came here on a Sunday morning to watch The Rise of Skywalker. We chose the first showing at 8 am to beat the crowds and to also have the rest of Sunday to enjoy other things. However, upon arrival we found the mall entrance locked. It was about 10 minutes to 8 am so I figured they'd just open the doors at 8 am on the dot. Well, 8 am passes and there's a growing crowd of other Star Wars fans waiting with me. Finally around 8:10 am one of the other moviegoers calls the Puente Hills Mall Security office to find out what's going on. It turns out AMC did not notify Mall Security that they had early morning showings! So we finally get in around 8:15 am and I rush over to grab a coffee before the movie starts. At this point I can hear the previews going on so I'm praying I don't miss the beginning of the movie. After taking my order and accepting my payment, the cashier turns to get my cup of coffee only to realize that the coffee machine was out of order. Ugh! I had to wait for the cashier to give me a refund which took another 3 - 4 minutes. Luckily I had reserved seating and I made it to my seat just in time for the start. This was my first time to this particular AMC, but I'm not a big fan of AMCs in general and this experience only re-affirmed my opinion of them.< /Text><Pictures>None</Pictures>< Response>

<userid>101193281181873753385< /userid><Name>Michael W</Name><Time>1536541681564</Time>< Rating>
3<//Rating>
< Review>
So, I wanted to give this place 4-stars because they put dividers in between the urinals in the bathroom, which is huge. The problem is they served some garlic knots hat were stale and in no way worth $7.

The theater entrance is inside the mall which is a bummer. Beyond that, the place has 2-6 ticketing windows operational with a couple self-serve stations (some of the best things ever made). The lobby is actually fairly large, with an expansive area leading left and right for the theaters, and straight for the snack bar. They have popcorn, candy, coke Freestyle machines, hot dogs, garlic knots, and a few other things. Prices as expected for a theater.

The seats were quite comfortable, with plenty of room in each seat for you to relax in. The automatic retracting is okay but it’s loud when trying to watch quiet scenes. Other than that, this is a great thing to have. Cramped theaters are awful.

Overall, I’ll probably go back to 4-stars if they get their garlic knots right!</Review>

<review>AMC Puente Hills 20 is one of the best AMC theaters that I’ve been to because the staff members are helpful and courteous, the auditoriums are always clean and well-kept, and I enjoy this location’s offering of both the Dolby Cinema and IMAX formats (plenty of other AMCs around the Rowland Heights area only offer standard digital, so this is definitely a plus!). The mall is still stuck in the 80's with Doc and Marty but the theater is pretty decent. Modern amenities like IMAX, ordering online, ticket kiosks, reserved recliner seats, and a bar. < text>
Overall, I had a mixed experience coming to this theater. As the other reviews say, the Dolby theater was very dirty. The seats we reserved was stained with popcorn and grease where the seat sparkled in the light. However, not other seats were like this. This just shows that the staff do not clean the theaters afterwards. I went to get some wet napkins to make it at least bearable to sit. However, the quality of the movie and sound was fantastic. The bass was so big that the whole theater shook (inside the theater there's at least 4 speaker lines on each side). I'll come back again as the movie experience is better than the stains I saw on the chairs.< /text>

<user_name>Nathan B</user_name>< Text>
This theater is dirty, cramped, and hasn't been upgraded since stadium seating was introduced to movie theaters.
The chairs dont recline or move at all, they are just straight back, uncomfortable seats.
I was going to a 10:30pm show, and myself and other guests were not allowed into the theater till 10:32pm, since they were still cleaning...and once in the theater, it looked like it hadn't seen a broom in weeks....popcorn everywhere,  trash on floor (and this was the supposed "IMAX theater" mind you.... which is the smallest IMAX I've ever seen. )
The lobby carpet was sticky.... which I had plenty of time to stand on, since I had to wait close to 20minutes in line for the concession stand, since the employees felt it necessary to help every premiere customer first,  ignoring all of us customers who dont want to pay more for faster/friendlier service (I say friendlier, due to employee being observed caring on and laughing with the premiere customer, but barely acknowledged my wife's and my existence,  but messed our order up as well.) The soda machines were out of practicality everything.
The bathroom was disgusting and smelled even worse.
The only thing this theater has going for it was that you can pick your seats....
Asked for a refund, since the overall experience did not make me want to stay for the film, and took almost 20min to accomplish that since was told to go see one employee,  who after waiting in line for, made me go see another, who then sent me back to second employee with message on how to do refund...
But that does nothing for me, since I won't return to this joke of a business.</Text>

<userid>114884398672720441810<//userid>< text>
Some of the best seats and offering are found in this theater.  Easy access from the lower level of the Puent Hills Mall, near Sears.  A bit of a walk from the Macy's 2nd floor entrance.

Large everything, with accommodations for long lines of theater goers, but well staffed with professional employees.  WIFI signal in that area is spotty or unusable. Since I am a "AMC Stubbs/A-List" member I have my ticket and seat assignment all on my phone, which they scan and cross check with your ID at the time you enter.  In a perfect world, that is how it works; with no WIFI you give your membership/phone number to a ticket seller and they give you a printed ticket.

Great experience with reclining seats in the IMAX theatre I sat in.< /text>
